http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Mysuru-to-host-BSNL-Athletics-Championship-from-today/article14009956.ece

More than 163 top sporting talents, from 18 telecom circles of Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd. (BSNL), will vie for top honours at the three-day 15{+t}{+h}All India BSNL Athletics Championship-2015-16, which begins here on Wednesday.The three-day annual sporting event, which is being hosted for the first time in Mysuru, will be inaugurated by former athlete Ashwini Nachappa at Chamundi Vihar Stadium here at 9 a.m.Chief General Manager, Karnataka Telecom Circle, P. Nagaraju and Principal General Manager, Mysuru Telecom District, K. L. Jairam will be present.The event is being jointly organised by the Karnataka Circle Sports and Cultural Board (KCSCB) and the District Sports and Cultural Board, Mysuru Telecom District. Nine sportspersons from the Karnataka telecom circle will be participating in the meet.Addressing a press conference here on Tuesday, Mr. P. Nagaraju said teams from Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, Assam, Chhattisgarh, Gujarat, Himachal Pradesh, Jharkhand, Kerala, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Odisha, Punjab, Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh and Uttarakhand are participating in the meet.Each team consists of participants (men and women), a coach and a manager.A total of 19 athletes had been nominated by the corporate office to assist and conduct the athletic meet. Mr. Jairam, who is the chairman of the event, said sportspersons were usually recruited by BSNL to encourage and promote sports.”Those who excel in tournaments like the one being conducted in Mysuru are sent to represent the nationals and other prestigious events on behalf of BSNL,” he said.Deputy General Manager Ganapathi Bhat, K Sampath Kumar and other officials were present.Sanchar Krida AwardThe Sanchar Krida Award, presented to the best sporting talent of Karnataka Telecom Circle, will be presented to Vikas M Putran from Mangaluru for athletics, during the 15th All India BSNL Athletics event-2015-16 which begins here on Wednesday.The three-day annual sporting event is being hosted for the first time in the city